fields.description:
*Assessment*

After doing a warm upgrade of a 4.0.0 cloud to 4.0.1 (with instances left running), the cloud was working just fine.  However, there was a scheduled switch outage that occurred shortly thereafter.  Information about the switch outage is as follows:
{quote}
Currently we have our PRC public and private switches chained together, one into the next. What I am proposing to do is add a new two switch stack, uplink the public/private switches into it, and then uplink it to the Force10. Doing this will increase performance, redundancy, and also provide us with tools to quickly identify and shut down network loops.
{quote}
After the outage, the autoscaling group associated with the Eucalyptus Imaging Worker seemed to run into issues communicating with the old autoscaling instance.  The autoscaling group therefore started another Eucalyptus Image Worker.  However, the old autoscaling instance has stayed in a 'shutting-down' state, even though its in a 'running' state on the NC.  All attempts to use 'euca-terminate-instances' failed.

*Signs*

* Output of 'euscale-describe-auto-scaling-groups verbose' before/after upgrade:
** Before
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# euscale-describe-auto-scaling-groups verbose
AUTO-SCALING-GROUP	asg-euca-internal-imaging-worker-01	lc-euca-internal-imaging-worker-01	ViciousLiesAndDangerousRumors		1	1	1	Default
INSTANCE	i-C60E610A	ViciousLiesAndDangerousRumors	InService	Healthy	lc-euca-internal-imaging-worker-01
AUTO-SCALING-GROUP	NginxScalingGroup	NginxLaunchConfig	ViciousLiesAndDangerousRumors	NginxLoadBalancer	0	0	0	Default
{code}
** After
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# euscale-describe-auto-scaling-groups verbose
AUTO-SCALING-GROUP	asg-euca-internal-imaging-worker-01	lc-euca-internal-imaging-worker-01	ViciousLiesAndDangerousRumors		1	1	1	Default
INSTANCE	i-3FE9880E	ViciousLiesAndDangerousRumors	InService	Healthy	lc-euca-internal-imaging-worker-01
AUTO-SCALING-GROUP	NginxScalingGroup	NginxLaunchConfig	ViciousLiesAndDangerousRumors	NginxLoadBalancer	0	0	0	Default
{code}

*Steps*

* Set up Eucalyptus 4.0.0 cloud, with Eucalyptus DNS, in Managed mode.
* Enable Eucalyptus Image Worker 
* Run a task that involves the Eucalyptus Image Worker (i.e. euca-import-instance or launch a paravirt EMI)
* After the task completes, perform warm upgrade (i.e. instances running) to Eucalyptus 4.0.1
* Confirm the upgrade is successful
* Power cycle the network switches associated with the cloud
* Check the behavior of the AutoScaling group associated with the Eucalyptus Image Worker

*Workaround*

Had to go onto the NC and terminate the instance using 'virsh destroy'.  Once I did that, the instance reported back to the CLC as terminated.
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# euca-describe-instances i-B4398933
RESERVATION	r-E28F6EB9	944786667073	euca-internal-imaging-worker-01
INSTANCE	i-B4398933	emi-6E93129B			terminated	euca-image-worker	0		m1.xlarge	2014-08-07T19:53:12.955Z	ViciousLiesAndDangerousRumors				monitoring-enabled					instance-store					hvm		a05dcc58-6cf1-4e20-99c5-f7dc36e65b49_ViciousLiesAndDangerousR_1	sg-A4E5958B			arn:aws:iam::944786667073:instance-profile/internal/imaging/imaging-worker-01
TAG	instance	i-B4398933	Name	euca-internal-imaging-workers
TAG	instance	i-B4398933	aws:autoscaling:groupName	asg-euca-internal-imaging-worker-01
{code}
fields.summary: After Switch Change, AutoScaling Group Spawns Un-Needed Instance; Old Instance Stays in 'Shutting Down' State
fields.environment:
* non-HA, single cluster
* 1 x CLC, DNS, Cloudformation
* 1 x UFS
* 1 x UFS, Walrus
* 1 x CC/SC (Overlay)
* 2 x NCs

comments.body: use case : shutdown the cc, then terminate an instance.
